HEADWORD: Oxybenzoic
<hw>Ox`y*ben*zo"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Oxy-</ets> <sd>(b)</sd> + <ets>benzoic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Hydroxybenzoic; pertaining to, or designating,
any one of several hydroxyl derivatives of benzonic acid, of which the
commonest is salicylic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

